cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use TAUT in research, benchmarks, or production deployments, please cite it as below."
title: "TAUT — Terse Agent Utterance Tuning"
abstract: "A one-file system prompt that compresses AI coding-agent prose output by 80% on average across 8 production agent CLIs (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Google Gemini, Factory Droid, Cursor, Pi, Hermes, OpenClaw) without persona collapse, character roleplay, or quality regression. Inspired by caveman (Brussee, 2026); diverges by replacing the caveman persona with a senior-engineer register."
type: software
